<article id="post-349" class="post-349 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-pop-culture category-travel tag-british-columbia tag-concerts tag-kelowna">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/04/david-bowie-kelowna-prospera-place/" rel="bookmark">David Bowie plays Kelowna Prospera Place</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>We all woke at about the same time. I was awake, though eyes closed, when I heard Tamara and Andrea whispering. I joined into the conversation, joined shortly thereafter by Dan. At that point, there wasn&#8217;t much reason to stay in bed, so I called first shower (I hadn&#8217;t had one since getting up &#8220;yesterday&#8221; in Japan).<br />
The plan had been to go for dim sum for breakfast, at the Chinese restaurant across the road. Not being open until 11:30 proved to be a bit of an issue, however, so we opted for breakfast #2: IHOP. Unlike Calgary, there is an International House of Pancakes in Kelowna. And we weren&#8217;t the only ones who knew that. The lineup was clearly out the door, and not just by a few people. It would be a long wait before we got breakfast if we&#8217;d stayed. We opted for the much shorter lineup at a nearby Perkins.<br />
It felt good to not eat Japanese for a change.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/04/david-bowie-kelowna-prospera-place/#more-349" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;David Bowie plays Kelowna Prospera Place&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/04/david-bowie-kelowna-prospera-place/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2004-04-11T17:17:24-06:00">11 April 2004</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/pop-culture/" rel="category tag">Pop Culture</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/travel/" rel="category tag">Travel</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/british-columbia/" rel="tag">british columbia</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/concerts/" rel="tag">concerts</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/kelowna/" rel="tag">kelowna</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/04/david-bowie-kelowna-prospera-place/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on David Bowie plays Kelowna Prospera Place</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
